@node install "INSTALLATION"
To use AddressManager you need an AMIGA with at least 512 KB (Is there anyone
having  only 512K?  I suppose not, but AddressManager should run anyway!) and
WB 2.0 or better.
AddressManager is rather  compact, so you will have no problems using it with
only one floppy, but a second one or a harddisk are of course also useful.
AddressManager was tested on A500(+),A1200 and A2000,but it should run on all
other AMIGAs too.

If you already own the INSTALLER you can use the "InstallAM"-Script.  It will
do all the work for you.


@{"WB 2.0-installation           " link wb20}
@{"WB 2.1 and better installation" link wb21}
@endnode

@node wb20 "WB 2.0"
You need a bootable disk or harddisk with at least 38KB free. You should also
have the ASL.LIBRARY in your libs:-directory and if you want to use the print
function also the PRINTER.DEVICE in your devs:-directory. 
To install AddressManager just copy it on this disk.
You should also have the ENV: and ENVARC: directories assigned if you want to
use the AddressManager-Prefs.

The program will run in English.If you would rather like to have it in German
you can:
- buy WB 2.1 or higher
- read @{"SHAREWARE" link share} and  @{"SERVICE" link service}
@endnode 

@node wb21 "WB 2.1 and better" 
Do the same as  described for WB 2.0,  but if you  want to use the program in
German language you should also:
- have some free KB more on your disk
- have the LOCALE.LIBRARY in your libs:-directory
- in your LOCALE:-directory have:

  - ASL.CATALOG  in   LOCALE:CATALOGS/DEUTSCH/SYS  and ADDRESSMANAGER.CATALOG
    in LOCALE:CATALOGS/DEUTSCH
    The second catalog can be found in the distribution-archive in the 
    CATALOGS/DEUTSCH-directory
    If you also want the REQTOOLS.LIBRARY to use German language, you have to
    have the appropriate catalog in your LOCALE:CATALOGS/DEUTSCH-directory.

AddressManager  will  only run in  German  language if you have this language 
among you prefered languages (LOCALE-Prefs) BEFORE English.
@endnode

@node config "CONFIGURATION"
There are 3 methods of configuring AddressManager:

- from the Workbench:

  - AddressManager uses  the  WB-Screen,  and  so  all  prefrences of  the WB 
    concerning resolution, colors, printer... will be taken over
  
- using the TOOLTYPES:

To change the  TOOLTYPES just click on the icon of  AddressManager  once  and 
call  INFORMATION  from  the  ICON-Menu of  the WB.  Now you  can  change the
TOOLTYPES:
  - DONOTWAIT  should  always be  there.  If you have AddressManager in  your 
    WBStartup-drawer so that it is started everytime you boot, this tooltype
    makes the WB not wait for the programs answer. 
  - POP_UP defines if the AddressManager window should be opened  immidiately
    after starting or not. If it is set to NO the program will only create an
    AppIcon  and  wait until you activate it.  This is  useful if you want to 
    have the program in the WBStartup-drawer.  Otherwise this tooltype should
    be set to YES.
  - MSGREQ=STD enforces standard requesters for messages
  - FILEREQ=ASL enforces ALS-filerequesters

- using the built-in-prefs.More about this in the chapter @{"USING ADDRESSMANAGER" link use}
@endnode  

@node use "USING ADDRESSMANAGER"
Starting:

- from the WB:

  Just double-click the  AddressManager-icon to start the program.If you want
  to load some data at the same time just click the AM-icon once, press SHIFT
  and double-click the icon of the data-file. 

- from the Shell:

  AddressManager [FILE]

  FILE can be some data-file which you want to be loaded together with AM.


Now you have started AddressManager. First some important information:

- AddressManager creates an  AppIcon on the WB.  If you  double-click  it the 
  AM-Window will come to front. 
  You can also drop an data-file-icon on the AppIcon to load it.
- AddressManager creates an AppWindow. Just drop an file into it, and it will
  be loaded.
- The number of people you  can manage is only limited by the  amount of free
  memory. You will need about 2.3KB for a person.
- The name and the surname of every person will appear in the list on left of
  the window. Just click on a name, and the corresponding data will appear in
  the string gadgets on the right side of the window.
- All gadgets have one underlined character. Just press the corresponding key
  to activate the gadget. The list of entries plays a special role here:
  - press just <x> to activate the next person
  - press <SHIFT>-<x> to activate the previous person

Now some information about the functions of the gadgets, menus and so on:

@{"CLOSE-gadget    " link close}
@{"ZOOM-gadget     " link zoom}
@{"NAME,SURNAME... " link name}
@{"EXISTING ENTRIES" link exist}
@{"NEW PERSON      " link new}
@{"DELETE          " link del}
@{"UPDATE          " link take}
@{"SAVE/LOAD       " link save}
@{"PRINT           " link print}
@{"PREFS           " link prefs}
@{"NEW             " link new}
@{"CLEAR           " link cl}
@{"PARAMETERS      " link para}
@{"SEARCH          " link search}
@{"GO ON           " link goon}
@{"MENUS           " link menus}
@endnode

@node new "NEW"
  Clears all.
@endnode

@node cl "CLEAR"
  Clears the String-gadgets.
@endnode

@node para "PARAMETERS"
  After activating this function a new window  appears.  Here you can type in 
  the criterion after which a person will be searched. You can use all joker-
  signs  like "#?" which  you  already  know  from the  Shell.  The searching 
  algorythm does not make any difference between normal and capital  letters.
  After finishing this just click on OK!.
  You  can also  switch  between the  gadgets by  pressing TAB (or RETURN) or 
  SHIFT-TAB.
@endnode

@node search "SEARCH"
  Now the list of people will be serched through from the beginning, and if a
  person fits all the conditions it will be activated and shown in the string
  -gadgets. Otherwise the message "Not found!" will be displayed.
@endnode

@node goon "GO ON"
  This  function  continues  searching  from the  position where it was  last 
  stopped  under  the  same  conditions. If you  have not  called the @{"SEARCH" link search}-
  function before, or if the whole list has already been searched this gadget
  shows no effects. 
@endnode

@node menus "Using of the menus"
  Some important functions can be called from the menu too.
  There are also functions only available from the menu:
   - ABOUT
     Shows some information about the program.
   - SAVE
     Saves under the old file-name without opening a requester.
@endnode

@node print "PRINT"
  After  calling  this  function an  requester will  appear in  which you can 
  if you want to print all the data, only the activated person or nothing.
  More about the actual printing is to be found under @{"PREFS" link prefs}.
  Additionally there is a possibilty of printing on envelopes.If you use this
  function only  the name,  the address and if you want also the country will
  be   printed.  The   auto-centering  of  your  printer  will  be  activated
  automatically.
@endnode

@node prefs "PREFS"
  The program can be configured here:
  
  - DIRECTORY
    Here you  can type  in  your working-directory.  If  possible  it will be 
    activated  everytime  you open a  file-requester until you  have selected 
    some other directory there.
    The short cut has two meanings:`D` activates the string-gadget, `d` opens
    a requester in which you can select the directory.

  - THAT WILL BE PRINTED:
    You can select an item in the listview-gadget and then :
    - PRINT if selected the active item will be printed
    - BOLD  if selected the active item will be printed bold
    - SEPARATE (only if HORIZONTAL activated) :
      - if activated the item will be separated from the next one by a line,
        otherwise by a space
    - CHARS (only if HORIZONTAL activated) : here you can say how many chars 
      of the complete line belong to this item. The sum of all items and
      separations cannot be higher then the lenght of a line of the printer

EXAMPLE:

Name       First name | Street            City           | Telephone 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
xxxx       xxx        | xxxxxx xxx x      xxx xxx x      | xxxx/xxxxx
yyyy       yyy        | yyyyy  yy  y      yyyyyy y y     | yyyyy/yyy

    10     10         ^ 20                15             ^ Rest
                      |                                  |
                 Separation                         Separation

The Printer-prefs look like this:
Pica (10cpi)
Left margin :2
Right Margin:78
So you have 76 columns for AddressManager-output. To get the same output as 
above you have to desactivate PRINT in BIRTHDAY,COUNTRY and REMARKS and set
CHARS to the following numbers:
Name      :10
First Name:10
Street    :20
City      :15 
Telephone :13  
You have also to activate SEPARATE in FIRST NAME and CITY.
 
    - If HEADERS is activated each line or column begins with NAME:, REMARKS:
      etc.
    - SURNAME FIRST makes the program print the surname before the first name
    - The gadget PRINT ONLY EXISTING ENTRIES has the following function:
      Usually a printing looks like this:

       NAME          : Michael Schikora
       BIRTHDAY      : 06.07.1974
       ADDRESS:
        STREET       : Chemnitzer Weg 1
        CITY         : 53119 Bonn
        COUNTRY      : Deutschland
      TELEPHON       : 110        ( <- DO NOT CALL, IT IS WRONG!!! )
      OTHER REMARKS  : The author of AddressManager

      If one of the entries i.e. OTHER REMARKS is empty a line like 

      OTHER REMARKS  :

      will be printed. If you want to suppress this activate ONLY EXISTING...
      If you have already suppressed the printing of some data by the NAME...
      -gadgets it will of course not be printed even if it exists.

  - SAVE
    The new  prefs will be  taken over  and  saved in  your ENV: and  ENVARC: 
    directories. Therefore they will be automatically activated next time you
    boot.
  - SAVE AS...
    You can save the configuration somewhere to use it later
  - LOAD
    Loads a saved configuration
  - USE  
    The new prefs will be taken over and saved in your  ENV:-directory. So it
    will be valid until you turn off your computer or reboot.
  - CANCEL
    The new prefs will neither be taken over nor saved.
@endnode

@node close "CLOSE-Gadget"
  Ends the  program after  asking if you really want to end it and giving you
  a chance to save your data.
@endnode

@node zoom "ZOOM-Gadget"
  This gadget  iconifies the program.  The  window is closed, but the data is 
  still in the memory.  You can re-open the window by activating the AppIcon,
  which is still on the WB.
@endnode

@node name "SURNAME,NAME..."
  In these gadgets you just type in the data. You can jump from one gadget to
  an other with TAB (or RETURN) or SHIFT-TAB. If you click on a person in the
  list the corresponding data will also appear here.
  If you leave the REMARKS-Gadget, you can press RETURN to add the  person in
  the string-gadgets to  your list, clear the gadgets and activate  the first 
  gadget automatically.  This makes it possible to enter several persons in a
  row very quickly.
@endnode

@node exist "EXISTING ENTRIES"
  The names and surnames of all people can be seen here.  Just click on  them 
  to recall the data.
@endnode

@node new "NEW PERSON"
  After you have typed all  the data about a  person into the  string-gadgets
  you  have to  use this  function to take it  over into the  actual  list of 
  people. The new entry will be inserted into the alphabetical list.
@endnode

@node del "DELETE"
  The last activated entry will be deleted.
  The entry above it will be activated automatically.
@endnode

@node take "TAKE OVER"
  If you want to change an existing entry, just  recall it by clicking  on it 
  in the list of  existing entries. Then  change the contents of the  string-
  gadgets. When you are satisfied with the new contents of these gadgets,just
  use TAKE OVER. The data in the actual list will be updated now.
@endnode

@node save "SAVE/LOAD"
  I suppose you already know what these functions are for!
  After  calling one of  them an ASL- or REQTOOLS-filerequester appears. Here
  you can select a directory and a file to load or save.
  If you use the REQTOOLS.LIBRARY you have also the possibility of creating a
  new directory in the SAVE-Requester. Just type the name of a directory that
  does not exist yet,and the requester will ask you if you want to create it.
  Before loading data AM checks if the previous data was changed since it was
  saved for the last time. If it was you have a last chance to save it now.
  Every saved file automatically gets an icon.
  The  saving-format is rather  compact, so  that you will need less place on 
  disk the in memory for the same amount of data.If you want more information
  about this  format  because you e.g. want to make your own  Manager-program
  compatible to AddressManager just write me.
@endnode

@node history "HISTORY"
- AddressManager V1.0 (07.11.1993) is the first publicated version.
- AddressManager V1.1 (20.11.1993) :
  - if  you  leave  any  string-gadget (in  the main window or in the SEARCH-
    window) by  pressing  RETURN the next gadget will be activated (suggested
    by Thortsen Schulz)
- AddressManager V1.2 (10.02.1994) :
  - fixed a bug: the PUBLICSCREEN is now correctly unlocked after leaving the
    program
  - a lot of small changes in the user interface:
    - all windows are  redesigned. They take less place on the screen now, so
      they even can be opened on a 640*200 screen (NTSC HighRes normal size)
    - ABOUT, PREFS and SEARCH windows are centered in the main window
    - if you use REQTOOLS.LIBRARY the requesters are better now:
      - all requesters are centered in the main window 
      - the SAVE-Requester allows you to create new directories
- AddressManager V1.3 (13.03.1994) :
  - the stack is now allocated automatically
  - removed an unnecessary string from the main window
  - changed the handling of the string gadgets in the main window,so that you
    can enter several persons in a row much faster now (see also @{"USING..." link name}) 
- AddressManager V1.4 (29.05.1994)
  - you can use a requester to select your prefered directory in the prefs
  - OS 3.0`s NewLookMenus are now used
  - fixed a minor bug: When iconified,  AddressManager  did not  release  the
    WB-Screen completely, so you could not e.g. change  the screen mode until
    you left AM.
- AddressManager V2.0 (13.06.1994):
  - new prefs, print and search functions
  - lots of intern optimizations
@endnode

